{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f46f7a74-fc4a-4fd8-8a71-bb11fefbb544","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since there's no existing file to modify, here's how to convert your page to compiled bindings:\n\n## Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe key change is adding:\n1. `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` — import the namespace\n2. `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — enables compiled bindings against that type\n\n## Catching binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings are validated at compile time by default. To **ensure** build failures on bad bindings, add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat binding warnings as errors -->\n    <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the MAUI diagnostic for binding path issues. With `x:DataType` set, any typo like `{Binding Themee}` will produce a compile-time error instead of silently failing at runtime.\n\n**Tip:** If you need to opt out for a specific binding (e.g., in a DataTemplate with a different runtime type), use `x:DataType=\"\"` to disable compiled bindings locally.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"76745968-b0cd-4ef6-ad7c-c87f709238f4","outputTokens":484,"requestId":"5038:1E6E:181341F:1ACF985:69FA8F77"},"id":"cee3967e-b763-4d54-885b-89445b1c7247","timestamp":"